> How do you do a newline here without sending the prompt to you? I've tried shift+enter, cmd+enter, alt+enter, but none of them work.

⏺ In most terminal-based applications like the Claude Code CLI, creating a newline without sending the message can be challenging since terminals typically interpret Enter/Return as "send
  command".

  For the Claude Code CLI specifically, there isn't a built-in keyboard shortcut to insert a newline without sending the message. This is a limitation of terminal-based interfaces.

  Some possible workarounds:
  1. Compose your message in a text editor first, then paste the entire message into the CLI
  2. Use a pipe to input from a file: cat your_message.txt | claude-cli
  3. Use the --input-file flag if available in your CLI version

  If you need to share this conversation, the simplest approach is still to select all text in your terminal window, copy it, and paste it into a file.

