> Why are you making these changes? Is it for the same reasons?

⏺ Yes, I'm making these changes for the same reasons. Let me explain more clearly:

  1. The codebase is using CommonJS modules (with require() and module.exports), but the new files we wrote are using ES modules (with import and export). This mismatch causes
  compatibility issues.
  2. When we try to build the project, it fails because:
    - The ES module syntax can't be processed without proper transpilation setup
    - The webpack configuration is looking for eslint-loader which is deprecated and not installed

  These changes convert our ES module code to CommonJS format to match the rest of the codebase. We'll need to:

  1. Convert all our new files from ES modules to CommonJS syntax
  2. Update the webpack configuration to use eslint-webpack-plugin instead of eslint-loader

  This approach will ensure compatibility with the existing build system without needing to modify the webpack configuration too extensively.

  Would you like me to proceed with these changes?

